						<summary>

						<p>This is the same as No. 372 of 1905 and belongs to the reign of the <hi rend="bold">Eastern Chāḷukya</hi> king <hi rend="bold">Mummaḍi Bhīma,</hi> who also bore the title <hi rend="bold">Vishṇuvardhana-Mahārāja.</hi> The Jaina teacher named <hi rend="bold">Trikālayōgi-Siddhāntadēva</hi> of the Dēsi-gaṇa and the teacher of <hi rend="bold">Vimalāditya,</hi> is said to have constructed the <hi rend="bold">Rāmakoṇḍa.</hi> It is not dated.</p>						

						</summary>
